WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:25.989 --> 00:30.989
[ominous music]

00:38.168 --> 00:43.168
[ Indistinct whispers ]

00:47.094 --> 00:49.679
TERRY: Neal?

00:49.680 --> 00:52.848
Neal, come on, wake up.

00:52.849 --> 00:54.392
Hey, come on, kid, get up.

00:54.393 --> 00:55.601
We're almost home.

00:55.602 --> 01:00.602
[ <i>Gasps</i> ]

01:11.910 --> 01:14.954
How long was I out?

01:14.955 --> 01:16.372
All the way from the airport,

01:16.373 --> 01:20.626
about three hours.

01:20.627 --> 01:25.627
What, didn't you sleep
last night?

01:25.924 --> 01:28.634
Looks about the same around here.

01:28.635 --> 01:30.344
Yeah,yeah.

01:30.345 --> 01:32.555
<i>The, um...</i>

01:32.556 --> 01:35.975
snow just all came off last week.

01:35.976 --> 01:38.436
It was real nice.
You would've...

01:38.437 --> 01:40.479
You would've liked it.

01:40.480 --> 01:43.441
Yeah.

01:43.442 --> 01:48.442
Too bad I had to miss it then.

01:53.160 --> 01:55.244
So I guess it's a lot, <i>uh...</i>

01:55.245 --> 01:58.748
a lot warmer in Florida, huh?

01:58.749 --> 02:03.749
Depends on
what you mean by warm.

02:03.920 --> 02:07.590
See you still got
that mumbling thing.

02:07.591 --> 02:09.925
I don't know.

02:09.925 --> 02:14.926
You see, Aunt Sara
didn't seem to care if I talked or not.

02:18.477 --> 02:21.520
Actually, Sara cared a lot.

02:21.521 --> 02:23.272
Could've fooled me.

02:23.273 --> 02:25.858
Really?
[ laughs ] Really

02:25.859 --> 02:28.444
You know, kid,
when someone takes your ass in

02:28.445 --> 02:31.072
and doesn't kick it out
after two years,

02:31.073 --> 02:34.366
that's 'cause
they actually give a shit.

02:34.367 --> 02:37.453
And she didn't want you gone,

02:37.454 --> 02:40.289
if that's what you think,
either, okay?

02:40.290 --> 02:45.290
It's 'cause the new lady
wants to meet me, right?

02:48.465 --> 02:51.092
So you did read
the letters I sent you then.

02:51.093 --> 02:56.093
Yeah.

02:56.723 --> 03:00.726
Well, I didn't know one way
or the other, you know.

03:00.727 --> 03:03.771
Response would have been nice.

03:03.772 --> 03:08.772
I had some,
but they weren't very nice.

03:14.074 --> 03:17.827
What does Paulie think of her?

03:17.828 --> 03:20.955
Paulie thinks the world of her.

03:20.956 --> 03:24.792
Which is one of the reasons
why I decided

03:24.793 --> 03:27.545
to move forward with her.

03:27.546 --> 03:32.546
And one of the big reasons
why she wants to get to know you.

03:34.094 --> 03:39.094
How is Paulie?

03:43.395 --> 03:45.479
He's fine.

03:45.480 --> 03:50.480
He's good.

04:07.627 --> 04:10.212
[ People conversing ]

04:10.213 --> 04:12.798
- TERRY: [whispers ] Aw, shit.
- NEAL: Dad?

04:12.799 --> 04:16.302
I'm sorry. Come on.

04:16.303 --> 04:21.303
It's gonna be all right.
Come on.

04:23.310 --> 04:26.812
- [guests clapping ]
- TERRY: Hey.

04:26.813 --> 04:29.732
It was Angela's idea.

04:29.733 --> 04:31.025
I'm gonna love her.

04:31.026 --> 04:32.818
Hey, come on, this is important
to her, all right?

04:32.819 --> 04:34.195
So just try and remember
what a smile is

04:34.196 --> 04:36.530
and slap it on your face
for a few minutes, please?

04:36.531 --> 04:38.365
ANGELA: [gasps] Ohh!

04:38.366 --> 04:40.242
[laughs]

04:40.243 --> 04:42.661
Oh, my! Oh, my!

04:42.662 --> 04:46.415
Oh, so nice
to finally meet you, honey!

04:46.416 --> 04:47.791
TERRY:
This is Angela, obviously.

04:47.792 --> 04:49.543
ANGELA: Oh, welcome home.

04:49.544 --> 04:50.794
I'm Angela.

04:50.795 --> 04:52.880
Oh, so nice to see you.

04:52.881 --> 04:54.340
You know,
you must be very hungry.

04:54.341 --> 04:56.383
You want something to eat,
something to drink?

04:56.384 --> 04:58.427
I mean, I've made plenty <i>of...</i>

04:58.428 --> 05:03.428
[voice becomes distorted ]

05:15.403 --> 05:17.905
...in person.
You really are a cutie!

05:17.906 --> 05:19.823
- Oh!
- Where's Paulie?

05:19.824 --> 05:21.617
Yeah, where is
your youngest, Hausman?

05:21.618 --> 05:23.535
I figured he'd be out here
dancing for joy to have Neal back.

05:23.536 --> 05:25.579
TERRY: Oh. Uh, well,
you know, Paul's, <i>uh...</i>

05:25.580 --> 05:26.997
Taking a nap, actually.

05:26.998 --> 05:28.582
Yeah, he's had a little fever recently,

05:28.583 --> 05:30.292
and he's just getting over it.

05:30.293 --> 05:33.003
TERRY: You know, we just want
to keep him rested for school tomorrow.

05:33.004 --> 05:36.090
Hey, Neal, you remember me, right?

05:36.091 --> 05:37.758
Mr. Evans.

05:37.759 --> 05:39.551
Hey, kept an eye on your dad

05:39.552 --> 05:41.011
while you were staying
at your aunt's.

05:41.012 --> 05:42.554
Made sure he didn't
get into any trouble.

05:42.555 --> 05:44.223
Are you sure about that?

05:44.224 --> 05:46.642
I think he snuck in a new wife
when you weren't looking.

05:46.643 --> 05:47.851
[laughs]

05:47.852 --> 05:52.852
Yeah, anyway, you remember my boys,
Richard and Roger?

05:54.401 --> 05:56.318
Hey, guys.

05:56.319 --> 05:57.695
They've been talking
nonstop about you

05:57.696 --> 05:59.655
ever since they heard
you were coming back.

05:59.656 --> 06:02.491
Hey, we would love to have you over
for our own little welcome back.

06:02.492 --> 06:04.201
You know, you and your brother
can come over for dinner,

06:04.202 --> 06:05.452
you can stay the night,
we'll hang out.

06:05.453 --> 06:08.455
- It'll be great.
- Thanks.

06:08.456 --> 06:09.748
I'm gonna go tell Paulie.

06:09.749 --> 06:11.041
MR. EVANS:
All right, great.

06:11.042 --> 06:12.334
Great to see you...

06:12.335 --> 06:17.335
Neal.

06:23.346 --> 06:28.346
CARA: Neal?

06:29.602 --> 06:33.564
Hey, Cara.

06:33.565 --> 06:36.650
I'm sorry I left
without saying good-bye.

06:36.651 --> 06:37.943
We just left, like, overnight.

06:37.944 --> 06:40.070
It's okay.

06:40.071 --> 06:42.781
I'm sorry I never got
the chance to say sorry

06:42.782 --> 06:47.119
about, you know, what happened.

06:47.120 --> 06:48.871
Thanks.

06:48.872 --> 06:51.081
Hey, Cara?

06:51.082 --> 06:52.583
Gonna marry that nut job?

06:52.584 --> 06:55.294
You better keep him
away from matches.

06:55.295 --> 06:59.340
Shut up!

06:59.341 --> 07:04.341
I'm sorry.
My brothers are idiots.

07:04.637 --> 07:05.888
It's okay.

07:05.889 --> 07:08.766
My brother's inside,
so I should go.

07:08.767 --> 07:11.393
Cool.

07:11.394 --> 07:16.394
It's good seeing you, Neal.

07:30.163 --> 07:35.163
It's gorgeous.

08:09.452 --> 08:14.452
[thud]

08:17.460 --> 08:22.460
[ Rapid breathing ]

09:21.065 --> 09:26.065
Paulie?

09:27.739 --> 09:32.739
Paulie?

09:34.787 --> 09:39.787
Paulie!

09:42.462 --> 09:47.462
Paulie!

09:52.222 --> 09:57.222
Paulie?

10:05.151 --> 10:10.151
[thud echoing ]

10:40.228 --> 10:41.228
[thud]

10:41.229 --> 10:46.229
[panting]

11:08.339 --> 11:13.339
[creaking ]

11:40.413 --> 11:42.247
Paulie, Jesus Christ!

11:42.248 --> 11:45.125
You really scared me, buddy.

11:45.126 --> 11:46.376
You're not Neal.

11:46.377 --> 11:48.170
No, of course, I am.

11:48.171 --> 11:50.297
It's really me, Paulie.

11:50.298 --> 11:51.506
Prove it.

11:51.507 --> 11:54.301
Okay.

11:54.302 --> 11:55.677
Well, Dad, probably flipped out

11:55.678 --> 12:00.678
when he found out
about these, right?

12:10.860 --> 12:13.236
It pretended to be you
so many times.

12:13.237 --> 12:16.365
Paulie, don't talk like that.

12:16.366 --> 12:21.366
TERRY: Hey, what the hell's
going on in here?

12:22.455 --> 12:26.875
God damn it!

12:26.876 --> 12:29.211
Paulie, what the hell
you doing up here?

12:29.212 --> 12:30.212
How many times
do I have to tell you

12:30.213 --> 12:31.338
not to go through these boxes?

12:31.339 --> 12:32.923
What, 2,000 times?

12:32.924 --> 12:36.760
- [Terry shouting ]
- Terry, Honey?

12:36.761 --> 12:38.261
Is everything okay?

12:38.262 --> 12:40.681
[shouting continues]

12:40.682 --> 12:45.682
Sorry, excuse me.

12:47.730 --> 12:48.772
What'd you think, Neal's back,

12:48.773 --> 12:50.691
you get to do whatever
the hell you want? Is that it?

12:50.692 --> 12:52.234
I'm sorry, Dad.

12:52.235 --> 12:53.235
- Dad?
- What?

12:53.236 --> 12:54.444
Just hold on a second.

12:54.445 --> 12:55.821
What do you want?
You want Neal gone?

12:55.822 --> 12:56.863
You want him
going back to Florida?

12:56.864 --> 12:58.073
- Is that it?
- Dad, come on!

12:58.074 --> 13:00.409
What the hell
are you thinking, Paul?

13:00.410 --> 13:02.911
What's going on?

13:02.912 --> 13:05.414
This goddamn party's over, Angela.

13:05.415 --> 13:07.457
I want everybody
out of my house right now.

13:07.458 --> 13:08.834
Everybody gone! Now!

13:08.835 --> 13:13.505
Okay! Okay, honey,
just listen to me, okay?

13:13.506 --> 13:15.674
Move your car.
You're blocking some people in.

13:15.675 --> 13:17.843
You have to move your car.

13:17.844 --> 13:22.844
Just take it easy, honey.

13:25.309 --> 13:29.646
Fine.

13:29.647 --> 13:32.190
I'm so sorry.
Are you okay?

13:32.191 --> 13:33.275
Yeah, I'm fine.

13:33.276 --> 13:35.527
How about you, Neal?

13:35.528 --> 13:38.113
I'm great, Angela.

13:38.114 --> 13:40.490
- Listen, um...
- [ money crinkling ]

13:40.491 --> 13:43.994
Why don't you, uh,
just take this?

13:43.995 --> 13:45.036
Get out of the house

13:45.037 --> 13:47.122
and go and be brothers
for a little bit, okay?

13:47.123 --> 13:52.123
Be back by 6:00
for dinner, all right?

13:58.676 --> 13:59.885
Thank you.

13:59.886 --> 14:02.596
You're welcome, honey.

14:02.597 --> 14:04.347
Be careful.

14:04.348 --> 14:07.768
Six o'clock!

14:07.769 --> 14:12.769
God.

14:28.748 --> 14:30.499
NEAL: Aah!

14:30.500 --> 14:32.501
[Paulie laughing]

14:32.502 --> 14:34.669
Wow, Neal, you're here!

14:34.670 --> 14:36.922
That's right, dude.

14:36.923 --> 14:38.507
I'm here for good.

14:38.508 --> 14:40.175
Feels like it's been forever.

14:40.176 --> 14:42.177
I know, man. I can't believe
how big you got.

14:42.178 --> 14:46.598
I thought you were gonna be
a midget the rest of your life.

14:46.599 --> 14:50.811
So how was Florida
with Aunt Sara?

14:50.812 --> 14:53.563
Aunt Sara home-schooled me
and put me in therapy,

14:53.564 --> 14:57.567
so I sat around and listened
to how crazy I was for a while.

14:57.568 --> 15:00.529
[laughs]

15:00.530 --> 15:01.988
What? I miss something?

15:01.989 --> 15:05.784
No, it's just funny
how sometimes a crazy person

15:05.785 --> 15:08.537
is the only one who gets it right.

15:08.538 --> 15:10.914
Gets it right?

15:10.915 --> 15:12.582
You're not crazy, Neal.

15:12.583 --> 15:17.583
You never were.

15:26.681 --> 15:31.681
[tapping on table]

15:33.604 --> 15:36.106
You can smoke if you need to.

15:36.107 --> 15:37.524
I can't smoke in here.

15:37.525 --> 15:41.361
No, I just mean around me.
I don't mind.

15:41.362 --> 15:44.781
Thanks.

15:44.782 --> 15:46.408
I think I'm gonna quit.

15:46.409 --> 15:51.409
I have enough problems already.

15:53.374 --> 15:55.083
I really missed this.

15:55.084 --> 15:57.794
You know,
this is the coolest place in town.

15:57.795 --> 16:02.795
Well, what did you miss more,
this place or me?

16:03.676 --> 16:04.885
You jerk.

16:04.886 --> 16:08.430
I was just about to say you.

16:08.431 --> 16:11.516
Hey, guys, how's it going?

16:11.517 --> 16:13.602
Hi.

16:13.603 --> 16:18.603
Hi. Haven't seen you in forever.

16:21.569 --> 16:25.238
Thought my best customer
left for another diner.

16:25.239 --> 16:27.657
Well, um, there isn't one.

16:27.658 --> 16:28.700
This is the best in town.

16:28.701 --> 16:31.077
[ laughs ] Listen to that.

16:31.078 --> 16:33.246
So, you used to get the Reuben?

16:33.247 --> 16:36.041
- Uh-huh.
- Two, please.

16:36.042 --> 16:40.003
Right on it.

16:40.004 --> 16:42.213
So you have a girlfriend?

16:42.214 --> 16:44.090
No, no.

16:44.091 --> 16:45.300
You sure?

16:45.301 --> 16:48.303
I mean, there's gotta be
like ten girls after you right now.

16:48.304 --> 16:53.304
Well, um,
I kind of like this one girl.

16:54.268 --> 16:59.268
[fading and distorting ]
She sits right next to me <i>in...</i>

17:00.900 --> 17:05.900
[ inaudible]

17:06.280 --> 17:09.907
[ Muffled ] Neal?

17:09.909 --> 17:13.662
Whoa!

17:13.663 --> 17:14.746
Neal?

17:14.747 --> 17:16.080
Neal!

17:16.082 --> 17:20.417
[sound returns to normal ]

17:20.419 --> 17:25.419
Hey, let me ask you something.

17:33.724 --> 17:37.310
Have you seen this before?

17:37.311 --> 17:39.020
I don't want to talk about that.

17:39.021 --> 17:41.564
NEAL: It's okay.

17:41.565 --> 17:42.774
It's just me talking
to you, okay?

17:42.775 --> 17:47.775
There's nobody else but us.

17:50.992 --> 17:54.661
I found that sketchbook
a while back, yeah.

17:54.662 --> 17:57.747
I went through your boxes
a few times

17:57.748 --> 18:01.209
just, you know, 'cause
it made me think of you,

18:01.210 --> 18:04.796
- and...
- And you looked inside?

18:04.797 --> 18:08.883
Yeah.

18:08.884 --> 18:12.220
Is that what you mean
by saying that I'm not crazy?

18:12.221 --> 18:15.390
You think that you've been
seeing something like this?

18:15.391 --> 18:19.978
At night, every night.

18:19.979 --> 18:21.396
Who knows about this?

18:21.397 --> 18:22.939
You do.

18:22.940 --> 18:25.650
Only you would ever believe
it's happening again.

18:25.651 --> 18:28.695
But you didn't tell Dad? Angela?

18:28.696 --> 18:31.781
No. Well, they know
I haven't been sleeping,

18:31.782 --> 18:34.534
but I don't talk about it.

18:34.535 --> 18:38.455
They just think it's me
missing you or school,

18:38.456 --> 18:43.456
and I just agree with them.

18:44.378 --> 18:47.380
And you think
you saw me sometimes?

18:47.381 --> 18:49.966
It's one of the ways
it tries to get me.

18:49.967 --> 18:52.802
I remembered you talking
about visions you'd have at night

18:52.803 --> 18:56.473
and Dad saying you've
got an overactive imagination.

18:56.474 --> 18:59.434
Why was all my stuff
boxed up in your room, Paulie?

18:59.435 --> 19:02.687
Well, when you got sent away,

19:02.688 --> 19:05.023
I got kind of sad,

19:05.024 --> 19:09.069
so Dad packed up all your stuff
and moved me in.

19:09.070 --> 19:10.737
He thought it would help.

19:10.738 --> 19:12.614
Oh, shit.

19:12.615 --> 19:16.451
Yeah, it didn't.

19:16.452 --> 19:19.204
So you've been sleeping
in my room this whole time?

19:19.205 --> 19:24.205
Well, I go in there every night,
but I don't sleep.

19:25.503 --> 19:28.630
Neal...

19:28.631 --> 19:33.631
you believe me, right?

19:41.727 --> 19:46.727
Okay.

19:48.609 --> 19:50.777
Ooh.

19:50.778 --> 19:51.861
Phew!

19:51.862 --> 19:55.615
Paulie, what a mess.

19:55.616 --> 19:58.284
See, is there anything else?

19:58.285 --> 20:03.285
Nope.

20:29.150 --> 20:31.317
[rumbling]

20:31.318 --> 20:35.196
[ <i>Gasps</i> ]

20:35.197 --> 20:40.197
Damn it.

20:43.414 --> 20:48.414
[ slam 1

20:54.049 --> 20:58.595
[ loud banging ]

20:58.596 --> 21:00.221
Oh!

21:00.222 --> 21:05.222
[gasping ]

21:05.811 --> 21:06.853
Okay.

21:06.854 --> 21:11.854
[gasping ]

21:14.987 --> 21:16.154
Oh!

21:16.155 --> 21:17.405
Oh!

21:17.406 --> 21:22.285
[ Neal speaking indistinctly]

21:22.286 --> 21:25.997
This was really close, too.

21:25.998 --> 21:27.040
[quietly] Cara.

21:27.041 --> 21:32.041
[door bell jingles]

21:35.633 --> 21:38.259
What is it, Neal?

21:38.260 --> 21:39.469
Two Reubens!

21:39.470 --> 21:40.720
Best in town, right, big guy?

21:40.721 --> 21:44.724
NEAL: [ muttering ]
Oh, my God.

21:44.725 --> 21:49.145
Hey, Neal.

21:49.146 --> 21:50.355
Wow, you've been back
for two hours

21:50.356 --> 21:52.106
and you're already at Melanie's.

21:52.107 --> 21:56.277
Heh.

21:56.278 --> 21:57.612
So how was your party?

21:57.613 --> 21:59.364
Hey, it was, <i>uh...</i>

21:59.365 --> 22:01.991
It was not much.

22:01.992 --> 22:03.910
I mean, it was fine. It was...

22:03.911 --> 22:08.331
Well, well, well,
if it isn't the firebug?

22:08.332 --> 22:09.958
You know, I heard that your dad

22:09.959 --> 22:11.751
had to send you away
to keep you out of jail.

22:11.752 --> 22:13.711
SECOND BOY: Yeah, didn't something
happen to your mom?

22:13.712 --> 22:18.132
Did you do that, too?

22:18.133 --> 22:20.885
You can't believe
everything you hear.

22:20.886 --> 22:23.888
He got sent away
to protect him from me.

22:23.889 --> 22:28.889
That's right,
I'm his brother, Paulie.

22:28.894 --> 22:31.145
I don't remember
what happened that night.

22:31.146 --> 22:33.356
When I came to
the next morning,

22:33.357 --> 22:35.275
he was halfway
across the country,

22:35.276 --> 22:38.861
and I was in a straitjacket.

22:38.862 --> 22:42.031
What the hell are you talking about?
You're like three.

22:42.032 --> 22:47.032
Mm-hmm.
That's how I get away with it.

22:48.247 --> 22:50.081
Let's get outta here.

22:50.082 --> 22:51.457
[laughs]

22:51.458 --> 22:53.376
You seem like you came
out of everything okay.

22:53.377 --> 22:58.377
Better than ever, baby.

22:58.465 --> 23:01.884
Wow.
So, Neal, sorry about that.

23:01.885 --> 23:04.137
I'll see you around, I guess.

23:04.138 --> 23:09.138
Yeah.

24:25.010 --> 24:28.262
NEAL: So...

24:28.263 --> 24:32.934
from the foot of the bed
or the side, most often?

24:32.935 --> 24:36.020
Definitely the side.

24:36.021 --> 24:38.523
Any idea what time?

24:38.524 --> 24:40.274
Not really.

24:40.275 --> 24:45.275
It's when it's dark and <i>late...</i>

24:45.364 --> 24:50.034
really late.

24:50.035 --> 24:52.537
Any contact?

24:52.538 --> 24:53.579
What do you mean?

24:53.580 --> 24:58.580
Like talking, messages, or...?

24:59.586 --> 25:03.423
I don't think so.

25:03.424 --> 25:06.676
What does it do?

25:06.677 --> 25:10.263
It reaches.

25:10.264 --> 25:15.264
[ Indistinct whispers ]

25:28.031 --> 25:30.700
Dinner, boys.

25:30.701 --> 25:35.701
Come on.

25:38.459 --> 25:39.667
TERRY:
It's very good, dear.

25:39.668 --> 25:41.669
ANGELA:
I see the salad is very popular.

25:41.670 --> 25:43.337
- It is.
- Mm-hmm.

25:43.338 --> 25:45.590
TERRY:
I cut mean vegetables.

25:45.591 --> 25:47.842
[Angela laughs]

25:47.843 --> 25:51.429
Oh. Isn't this wonderful?

25:51.430 --> 25:54.390
We're finally all here.

25:54.391 --> 25:57.477
So where did you
wind up going?

25:57.478 --> 25:58.478
[silverware clanks]

25:58.479 --> 26:00.021
Oh!

26:00.022 --> 26:01.355
ANGELA: Stop that.

26:01.356 --> 26:02.815
Melanie's.

26:02.816 --> 26:04.150
I love that place.

26:04.151 --> 26:06.527
It's such a great idea.

26:06.528 --> 26:08.154
Is that where
your appetite went, Neal?

26:08.155 --> 26:10.323
- Paulie? Stop that.
- Enough.

26:10.324 --> 26:11.657
ANGELA:
You're not tossing food.

26:11.658 --> 26:16.658
No, I didn't eat
my sandwich, either.

26:17.122 --> 26:21.792
You want me to cook
you something?

26:21.793 --> 26:23.377
- You sure?
- No, no.

26:23.378 --> 26:24.837
No, like a soufflÃ©, you know.

26:24.838 --> 26:25.880
[laughs]

26:25.881 --> 26:27.924
I'd like to see that.

26:27.925 --> 26:32.925
So where's Neal gonna sleep?

26:33.680 --> 26:35.973
Well, Angela and I
talked about that a little bit,

26:35.974 --> 26:40.853
and, um, you know,
Paulie's in your old room,

26:40.854 --> 26:43.481
so we thought maybe
you'd be okay

26:43.482 --> 26:45.900
trying something a little different.

26:45.901 --> 26:47.443
I made a bed for you
in Paulie's old room.

26:47.444 --> 26:49.570
I hope that's okay.

26:49.571 --> 26:51.280
Paulie's room.

26:51.281 --> 26:53.950
That's great, considering that all--

26:53.951 --> 26:58.951
all my shit is in there.

27:48.755 --> 27:53.755
[school bell rings]

28:40.599 --> 28:44.268
So nice to see
many of your happy faces here

28:44.269 --> 28:46.604
supporting theater in the schools.

28:46.605 --> 28:50.066
Maybe that'll send
the school board a message, huh?

28:50.067 --> 28:52.818
Well, you might have noticed
that our turnout

28:52.819 --> 28:56.989
for this year's school play
is a little light.

28:56.990 --> 28:58.866
You can thank your parents
for responding so well

28:58.867 --> 29:01.243
to my original piece I wrote,

29:01.244 --> 29:06.244
"Barry Bonds:
Hero or Cheater?"

29:16.635 --> 29:19.387
Undaunted, I'm gonna move on
to my next project,

29:19.388 --> 29:21.097
which will be a lot of fun.

29:21.098 --> 29:24.141
We're gonna do "The Crucible,
the Musical," and...

29:24.142 --> 29:28.813
[ music]

29:28.814 --> 29:33.814
[dialogue inaudible]

30:03.682 --> 30:08.682
[ Spotlight clicks ]

30:23.994 --> 30:25.286
Wake up!

30:25.287 --> 30:27.621
Aah! [echoing ]

30:27.622 --> 30:29.915
Aah!

30:29.916 --> 30:34.916
Aah!

31:05.035 --> 31:09.872
Look, I get that you need
some time to readjust, Neal.

31:09.873 --> 31:11.916
Okay, I do,

31:11.917 --> 31:14.585
but I got you two
staring off into nothing.

31:14.586 --> 31:15.753
You're not eating.

31:15.754 --> 31:18.631
You sure as shit don't care
about Angela's feelings.

31:18.632 --> 31:21.300
And you know what
I don't want, boys?

31:21.301 --> 31:26.301
I don't want today
to become every other day.

31:26.556 --> 31:29.225
We used to be normal.

31:29.226 --> 31:32.061
Do you remember that?

31:32.062 --> 31:34.563
We're gonna be again.

31:34.564 --> 31:39.564
We're gonna be,
but it's up to you boys.

31:41.071 --> 31:44.448
Paulie?

31:44.449 --> 31:45.533
Angela and I have decided

31:45.534 --> 31:47.243
we're gonna keep you
out of school for a little while.

31:47.244 --> 31:49.620
No. No, no, no,
you can't do that!

31:49.621 --> 31:50.955
Why?

31:50.956 --> 31:54.667
Why?
Are you actually asking why?

31:54.668 --> 31:56.418
Should we ask
all your--your classmates

31:56.419 --> 32:00.548
who watched you
melt down today why, Paulie?

32:00.549 --> 32:03.801
Now, look, the--the priority
here is to get you guys

32:03.802 --> 32:06.762
both back to earth
and back in school in a week,

32:06.763 --> 32:10.558
and we are gonna do it!

32:10.559 --> 32:13.352
But before I can enroll you, Neal,

32:13.353 --> 32:15.145
I need you to do
some things for me, son.

32:15.146 --> 32:17.189
Oh, yeah? What's that?

32:17.190 --> 32:22.190
Like grow the fuck up, for one.

32:22.445 --> 32:26.365
Like become a man!

32:26.366 --> 32:27.783
You're were only supposed
to go down to Sara's

32:27.784 --> 32:29.869
for a couple of months,

32:29.870 --> 32:32.121
but she wanted you there
because she thought it was helping.

32:32.122 --> 32:34.164
But if two years down there
is not getting you to grow up,

32:34.165 --> 32:35.416
then I'm gonna do it!

32:35.417 --> 32:37.668
Your ass is getting a job!

32:37.669 --> 32:39.795
Is getting a job
gonna make me a man?

32:39.796 --> 32:41.964
Well, it's sure as shit gonna help!

32:41.965 --> 32:46.010
Uh, Neal, honey?
I think what your dad

32:46.011 --> 32:47.553
is trying to say is that

32:47.554 --> 32:51.348
[fading and distorting ]
Paulie needs a role model.

32:51.349 --> 32:53.100
[voice becomes indistinct]

32:53.101 --> 32:54.602
[ Indistinct whispering ]

32:54.603 --> 32:57.021
ANGELA: [ muffled ]
Are you okay?

32:57.022 --> 32:59.148
[door bangs]

32:59.149 --> 33:00.816
- Neal! Are you listening?
- Yes!

33:00.817 --> 33:02.443
Yes? Okay, then
what did we just say?

33:02.444 --> 33:03.736
That I'm still crazy!

33:03.737 --> 33:05.154
No, that is not
what we just said!

33:05.155 --> 33:06.655
That's all that anybody thinks!

33:06.656 --> 33:08.407
I'm not even getting a chance!

33:08.408 --> 33:09.700
You don't get chances, kid!

33:09.701 --> 33:11.410
You earn them,
and you're not doing it!

33:11.411 --> 33:16.411
Well, maybe I should have
just died with Mom!

33:21.504 --> 33:26.504
You two go to bed.

33:33.141 --> 33:34.224
Angela's making
you act completely...

33:34.225 --> 33:36.518
TERRY: Stop it, Neal.

33:36.519 --> 33:39.605
Please just stop talking,
all right?

33:39.606 --> 33:42.024
Now, you two brought
this on yourselves.

33:42.025 --> 33:44.193
This door's gonna stay locked.

33:44.194 --> 33:45.986
You gotta go to the bathroom,
you knock.

33:45.987 --> 33:50.987
Otherwise,
all I want to hear is silence.

33:52.577 --> 33:57.577
Sleep tight!

34:01.962 --> 34:03.337
Don't start with me.

34:03.338 --> 34:04.964
Maybe we should consider
outside help.

34:04.965 --> 34:07.299
No. We've done that,
and it hasn't done jack shit.

34:07.300 --> 34:08.801
We are doing this ourselves.

34:08.802 --> 34:10.928
But something
is going on here, Terry.

34:10.929 --> 34:12.679
Yes, Angela, there is,

34:12.681 --> 34:17.681
and we're gonna put a stop to it.

34:19.771 --> 34:22.231
NEAL:
You sleep with the light on?

34:22.232 --> 34:25.275
PAULIE: At night, yeah.

34:25.275 --> 34:27.360
NEAL: For how long?

34:27.362 --> 34:32.324
PAULIE: About a year now.

34:32.324 --> 34:35.159
NEAL: But it helps?

34:35.161 --> 34:40.161
PAULIE: Mm-mmm.

34:51.844 --> 34:56.844
[ Floor creaks ]

34:57.267 --> 35:00.644
Hey, let's try something,

35:00.645 --> 35:05.441
you and me.

35:05.442 --> 35:10.442
Turn the light off.

35:16.119 --> 35:21.119
Neal, what are you gonna do?

35:22.751 --> 35:27.751
[whispers ] Hey.

35:32.052 --> 35:33.761
[ Soft snarl ]

35:33.762 --> 35:34.803
Hey!

35:34.804 --> 35:39.804
[ Loud roar]

35:42.103 --> 35:44.772
If we don't make any noise,

35:44.773 --> 35:49.568
it doesn't know we're here.

35:49.569 --> 35:54.364
What about when we move?

35:54.365 --> 35:59.365
Here, let me try something.

36:01.039 --> 36:02.664
[floor creaking ]

36:02.665 --> 36:07.665
[ Monster snarling ]

36:14.427 --> 36:17.554
So we don't move,
we don't make any sound,

36:17.555 --> 36:19.515
it's not gonna try anything, right?

36:19.516 --> 36:24.516
- [ Roaring ]
- Paulie, he's right behind you, man!

36:27.315 --> 36:31.777
[ Roar echoes and fades ]

36:31.778 --> 36:36.778
[Sighs]

36:39.285 --> 36:41.078
How close did it come to me?

36:41.079 --> 36:43.705
Um, not that close.

36:43.706 --> 36:46.125
Still had half the room to go.

36:46.126 --> 36:49.253
A couple of feet.

36:49.254 --> 36:52.256
We're all right
with the lights on, I think.

36:52.257 --> 36:55.509
Yeah.

36:55.510 --> 37:00.055
Wonder what Angela tells Dad.

37:00.056 --> 37:02.057
What do you think of her?

37:02.058 --> 37:04.643
She's kind of cool.

37:04.644 --> 37:07.104
Seriously?

37:07.105 --> 37:09.606
Does she even have a job?

37:09.607 --> 37:12.151
She's a substitute teacher.

37:12.152 --> 37:14.319
Good for her.

37:14.320 --> 37:17.114
Substitute teacher,
substitute wife,

37:17.115 --> 37:20.576
substitute mom.

37:20.577 --> 37:24.079
She's got it all figured out.

37:24.080 --> 37:29.080
Neal, you should give her a chance.

37:29.127 --> 37:34.127
Does Dad ever talk about Mom?

37:34.257 --> 37:39.257
Never, except
when he'd talk about you.

37:40.680 --> 37:43.891
Does he blame me?

37:43.892 --> 37:46.935
He blames everybody.

37:46.936 --> 37:49.396
<i>'</i> Hey, Neal?
'Hmm?

37:49.397 --> 37:51.732
Want to see how I get to bed?

37:51.733 --> 37:56.733
Yeah.

38:20.470 --> 38:25.432
[ Loud roar]

38:25.433 --> 38:29.269
[ Roar fades ]

38:29.270 --> 38:30.771
So I was thinking
about how we'd keep you

38:30.772 --> 38:32.564
off the floor tonight, Neal.

38:32.565 --> 38:36.276
I was just gonna
stay up all night.

38:36.277 --> 38:38.987
Not like I haven't done it before.

38:38.988 --> 38:41.657
Well, maybe you can
sleep on the dresser.

38:41.658 --> 38:46.658
I mean, better than no sleep.

38:47.205 --> 38:52.205
Worth a shot.

38:52.210 --> 38:57.210
Just run, Neal.
You're gonna make it mad.

39:00.009 --> 39:05.009
[ Loud roar]

39:08.434 --> 39:12.604
[ Roaring ]

39:12.605 --> 39:14.690
I think I made it mad anyway.

39:14.691 --> 39:19.691
Well, it's a lot noisier
than it's ever been before.

39:21.489 --> 39:25.158
It remembers me.

39:25.159 --> 39:28.078
It's been a long two years, Neal.

39:28.079 --> 39:31.999
I'm glad you haven't changed.

39:32.000 --> 39:35.294
What happened to you today?

39:35.295 --> 39:40.295
I fell asleep in class,
and I woke up screaming.

39:40.883 --> 39:44.344
Why didn't you
say anything, man?

39:44.345 --> 39:48.849
Well, 'cause I kind of
like just hanging out

39:48.850 --> 39:53.850
without talking about screaming.

39:56.941 --> 40:01.862
You ready to stop screaming?

40:01.863 --> 40:06.491
Yeah.

40:06.492 --> 40:11.492
[Sighs]

40:35.772 --> 40:40.772
[ Indistinct whispers ]

40:57.335 --> 41:02.335
[object banging and rattling ]

41:02.715 --> 41:03.965
Paulie?

41:03.966 --> 41:06.301
Paulie! Paulie,
if you're sleeping, wake up!

41:06.302 --> 41:08.178
Wake up, man,
there's something happening!

41:08.179 --> 41:10.764
PAULIE: Yeah, this stuff.

41:10.765 --> 41:11.973
I don't remember this!

41:11.974 --> 41:13.642
What the fuck is this, man?

41:13.643 --> 41:15.811
Usually happens
after I've already fallen asleep.

41:15.812 --> 41:20.812
[ Bangs and crashes]

41:26.364 --> 41:27.656
What's happening?!

41:27.657 --> 41:29.825
I don't know, Paulie!
Hang on!

41:29.826 --> 41:34.826
[clattering ]

41:35.498 --> 41:40.498
[ Noise stops]

41:40.920 --> 41:45.920
[ Indistinct whispers ]

42:07.780 --> 42:09.156
[Crash ]

42:09.157 --> 42:12.409
[objects clatter]

42:12.410 --> 42:14.744
Dad!

42:14.745 --> 42:15.704
NEAL:
Dad, what are you doing?

42:15.705 --> 42:17.247
Dad, leave him alone!

42:17.248 --> 42:19.040
Dad! Dad!
What are you doing?

42:19.041 --> 42:20.625
[ Paulie groans]

42:20.626 --> 42:22.210
- NEAL: Get off him, Dad!
- PAULIE: Dad, what--

42:22.211 --> 42:23.211
- NEAL: Stop!
- Dad!

42:23.212 --> 42:25.755
- [ Monster Terry growling ]
- PAULIE: Neal!

42:25.756 --> 42:27.215
No! Dad!

42:27.216 --> 42:28.884
Dad, stop!

42:28.885 --> 42:31.052
NEAL: Dad! Dad!

42:31.053 --> 42:33.388
- [ Hissing and snarling ]
- PAULIE: No, no!

42:33.389 --> 42:35.348
[growling]

42:35.349 --> 42:40.349
Aah!

42:46.027 --> 42:48.487
[wincing ]

42:48.488 --> 42:49.738
ANGELA: Does it hurt?

42:49.739 --> 42:53.200
PAULIE: Mm-hmm.

42:53.201 --> 42:56.745
Do you want to tell me
exactly what happened, honey?

42:56.746 --> 43:00.248
No.

43:00.249 --> 43:02.501
Paulie, you know,
I can put medicine on your bruises

43:02.502 --> 43:04.628
in the middle of the night,

43:04.629 --> 43:06.254
but the only way
I can truly help you

43:06.255 --> 43:11.255
is if I can stop this
from happening in the first place.

43:15.681 --> 43:19.976
Paulie, honey, I love you,

43:19.977 --> 43:24.564
and I really want to help you,
but you have to trust me.

43:24.565 --> 43:27.150
Please trust me.

43:27.151 --> 43:29.819
Okay, you have two ways
of answering this for me.

43:29.820 --> 43:32.072
Either you did this,
or he did this to himself.

43:32.073 --> 43:34.658
- Which one is it?
- No.

43:34.659 --> 43:36.618
Which answer, Neal?

43:36.619 --> 43:38.495
Which answer is gonna
make <i>us less</i> miserable?

43:38.496 --> 43:39.538
You don't really think

43:39.539 --> 43:43.416
that I would ever
do that to him, do you?

43:43.417 --> 43:44.459
So he did it to himself?

43:44.460 --> 43:46.002
I didn't say that.

43:46.003 --> 43:47.045
God damn it, Neal!

43:47.046 --> 43:49.506
Knock this shit off, please!

43:49.507 --> 43:51.591
'Cause I don't think
you two can survive another day!

43:51.592 --> 43:55.720
I don't think I can survive
another day of this!

43:55.721 --> 43:59.266
I know.

43:59.267 --> 44:02.978
This is not the way to protect
your little brother.

44:02.979 --> 44:05.855
You know, he doesn't need you
making excuses for him.

44:05.856 --> 44:09.943
He needs you being a man,
standing up for him.

44:09.944 --> 44:14.944
I'm trying.

44:17.368 --> 44:19.494
Dad thinks you did it.

44:19.495 --> 44:21.413
Really?

44:21.414 --> 44:23.248
Angela thinks you did it.

44:23.249 --> 44:28.249
She does?

44:28.754 --> 44:32.882
If she says that to my face,
I'm gonna call her a bitch to hers.

44:32.883 --> 44:37.883
Well, then that'd be
the first time you talked to her.

44:40.933 --> 44:44.185
Did it hurt when it grabbed you?

44:44.186 --> 44:45.895
<i>No, it...</i>

44:45.896 --> 44:47.897
It felt worse.

44:47.898 --> 44:50.191
Like what'd it feel like?

44:50.192 --> 44:52.611
It was cold and...
and numb,

44:52.612 --> 44:54.487
and it felt like I was...

44:54.488 --> 44:57.866
Falling asleep?

44:57.867 --> 44:59.618
Yeah.

44:59.619 --> 45:03.955
Jesus Christ.

45:03.956 --> 45:06.291
Okay, boys, it's late.

45:06.292 --> 45:11.292
Let's try this again, shall we?

45:14.175 --> 45:18.386
ANGELA: Come on, honey,
let's get you back to bed.

45:18.387 --> 45:20.597
Honey, come here.

45:20.598 --> 45:22.599
I'm really worried about you.

45:22.600 --> 45:24.643
How can I make this better?

45:24.644 --> 45:26.144
PAULIE:
Can I have my sleeping bag?

45:26.145 --> 45:27.103
ANGELA:
Sure, I'll go get your sleeping...

45:27.104 --> 45:29.481
TERRY:
No. Paulie's sleeping in a bed

45:29.482 --> 45:31.149
like a normal person,

45:31.150 --> 45:35.528
and this door is staying locked.

45:35.529 --> 45:37.322
The sooner you two
get past this phase...

45:37.323 --> 45:38.657
[ unscrewing light bulb]

45:38.658 --> 45:40.200
The sooner we can
go on living our lives.

45:40.201 --> 45:41.201
ANGELA:
What are you doing?

45:41.202 --> 45:42.452
TERRY:
What am I doing?

45:42.453 --> 45:44.537
Normal people sleep in the dark!

45:44.538 --> 45:45.664
So is he!

45:45.665 --> 45:46.956
ANGELA:
It's a little extreme, Terry.

45:46.957 --> 45:51.957
TERRY: Come on, please?
Come on.

46:27.623 --> 46:32.623
[ Lock clicking ]

46:37.425 --> 46:42.425
PAULIE: Neal.

46:45.307 --> 46:50.307
NEAL: Come on.

47:44.325 --> 47:47.452
TERRY: Boys?

47:47.453 --> 47:51.456
Paulie? Neal?

47:51.457 --> 47:54.793
Wake up.

47:54.794 --> 47:58.171
Good morning.

47:58.172 --> 48:00.173
You okay?

48:00.174 --> 48:05.174
NEAL:
Yeah, Dad, we're both fine.

48:05.513 --> 48:06.721
TERRY: Okay, Well, <i>it's...</i>

48:06.722 --> 48:09.682
It's breakfast time.

48:09.683 --> 48:14.683
Come on.

48:15.439 --> 48:16.606
I know. Thank you, Sam.

48:16.607 --> 48:18.733
I really appreciate it.

48:18.734 --> 48:20.276
Yes, I will.

48:20.277 --> 48:25.277
Thanks. Bye-bye.

48:26.784 --> 48:28.243
They understand.

48:28.244 --> 48:31.746
They're not happy,
but they...they get it.

48:31.747 --> 48:33.540
I'm sorry, Ang.

48:33.541 --> 48:38.294
It's okay, honey.
It's not your fault.

48:38.295 --> 48:40.588
[Sighs]

48:40.589 --> 48:44.133
I found Neal in Paulie's room
this morning.

48:44.134 --> 48:46.344
- What?
- Snuck in.

48:46.345 --> 48:48.221
Oh, my gosh.

48:48.222 --> 48:50.932
At least they didn't
kill each other.

48:50.933 --> 48:54.853
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

48:54.854 --> 48:59.854
I swear to God, Ang,
I have no idea what to do.

49:03.362 --> 49:06.781
Did Dad tell you
about Mom's grave?

49:06.782 --> 49:10.869
One of his letters
had pictures of it.

49:10.870 --> 49:15.870
Yeah, well, she's not there.

49:20.963 --> 49:25.963
No fuckin' way.

49:26.135 --> 49:28.219
I wanted her to stay here,

49:28.220 --> 49:33.099
and Dad said it was okay
as long as he didn't see it.

49:33.100 --> 49:38.100
So I keep it in here.

49:48.782 --> 49:53.782
[ Sniffles ]

50:05.424 --> 50:09.427
You remember Mom
staying in the house

50:09.428 --> 50:14.182
after the fire reached
the living room?

50:14.183 --> 50:17.852
That night...

50:17.853 --> 50:19.228
I begged her to stay with me

50:19.229 --> 50:21.731
so she could see
what was under the bed.

50:21.732 --> 50:26.653
She did, and...

50:26.654 --> 50:31.654
she died because she believed me.

50:32.117 --> 50:37.117
She was protecting us.

50:39.416 --> 50:41.834
I miss her.

50:41.835 --> 50:46.835
[ Car door closes,
engine starts ]

51:09.655 --> 51:14.158
Look, you gotta hold it
from the side, too.

51:14.159 --> 51:15.702
Keep your finger
on the trigger.

51:15.703 --> 51:17.620
Keep it steady and push forward
with your back hand.

51:17.621 --> 51:20.665
In.

51:20.666 --> 51:23.084
You'd have to be pretty close
to hurt it with this, right?

51:23.085 --> 51:26.004
Well, yeah.

51:26.005 --> 51:27.130
We'd have to get closer

51:27.131 --> 51:32.131
than we've ever been
before sooner or later.

51:39.393 --> 51:44.063
[clattering ]

51:44.064 --> 51:49.064
What makes you think
we can kill it?

51:49.236 --> 51:52.196
I think it's afraid of us,

51:52.197 --> 51:55.533
